在十三章三節說道:「你只要行善,就可得到他的稱相。」

94
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:35,000
這裡說到他是一個掌權者,說到我們和政權之間的關係。

95
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:56,000
所以保羅所說的善不是抽象的東西,而是我們和神、人、仇敵、政權的關係處境所實踐出來的。

96
00:18:56,000 --> 00:19:06,000
除了這些處境之外,保羅用羅馬教會的一些真實例子去展示我們什麼叫做好。

97
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:21,000
當時的羅馬教會有些信心軟弱的人,他們是不敢吃肉的,他們只吃菜。

98
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:31,000
他們覺得那些拜過偶像的肉是不潔淨的。

99
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:47,000
而另一班信徒,他們覺得什麼都可以吃的,所有東西都是屬於神,不需要潔淨。

100
00:19:47,000 --> 00:20:07,000
所以他們彼此體諒就沒有問題了,但是那些人就經常去爭辯那些是好,那些是不好的。

101
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:17,000
保羅就說,這些什麼都吃的人就不要去看低一些不吃的人,不吃的人就不要去說那些吃的人不對。

102
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:29,000
他甚至會提出你究竟是誰,為什麼要去論斷主內的人呢?

103
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:36,000
問題的重點不是因為那個食物。

104
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:48,000
因為神的國在乎吃喝,在乎公義和平。

105
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:31,000
我想用今天一些例子來看,就是神的國不在乎今天你去哪裡喝茶,你用的廁紙夠不夠柔軟,或者唱你的詩歌是新歌還是舊歌呢?

106
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:47,000
保羅說不要再彼此論斷,因為這個「再」字是很重要的,是代表爭辯了一段時間,因為一些不重要的事情是破壞了神的工作。

107
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:57,000
例子講了這麼久之後,那究竟什麼是好呢?

108
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:18,000
牧師就想起一段講道,就是大概在他十七八歲的時候,可能不是很久以前的事情,因為那個講道的訊息一直在他的腦裏面。

109
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:31,000
他想起當時他們教會去經拜裏面的一些轉變。

110
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:42,000
當時的教會是由鋼琴去唱一些傳統的詩歌轉變,用到吉他,鼓,貝斯,或者電子琴。

111
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:52,000
牧師當時就這麼說:

112
00:22:52,000 --> 00:23:07,000
當時有人提出質疑,牧師是不是因為他喜歡轉了這個敬拜的風格,是因為他喜歡夾Band?

113
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:16,000
但如果知道他熟悉的人,也知道牧師其實不夾Band的。

114
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:22,000
其實他就喜歡去拉二胡,

115
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:32,000
那可不可以因為我喜歡拉二胡,在這個音樂敬拜上去拉二胡呢?

116
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:49,000
或者我在敬拜裏面去拉二胡,彈琵琶,或者一些中樂。

117
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:58,000
去夾Band就是因為年輕人更加容易去接受,最重要不是一個音樂的形式,而是他們去敬拜的心。

118
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:12,000
We often think of good as a thing, a project, a plan, or a method.

119
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:21,000
Then we analyze it, compare, and look for the best solution.

120
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:30,000
But Paul's good isn't a thing, it's about how we live as a person.

121
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:48,000
It's something which we think is so good, hurt others, or cause someone to stumble, it is no longer that good.

122
00:24:48,000 --> 00:25:08,000
In the book of Romans, good is not a program, it's not an event, it's not a budget, not even a product.

123
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:26,000
Paul's good is doing God's good will in our relationships. Being a good person who cares for others, builds others up, and loves one another, becoming such a person is truly good.

124
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:53,000
See in church, people talk a lot about evangelism. But if we always fight with little things, new believers may come and get scared and go.

125
00:25:53,000 --> 00:26:04,000
So what is a good church? What is a good person in church?

126
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:12,000
Let Paul's conclusion in Romans 15 to be our conclusion.

127
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:29,000
We who are strong ought to bear the failings of the weak, and not to please ourselves. Each of us should please our labor for their good, to build them up.

128
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:57,000
We who are strong ought to bear the failings of the weak, and not to please ourselves. Each of us should please our labor for their good, to build them up.

129
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:07,000
這裏講到的堅強只是有能力,有空間的人願意去分擔沒有能力,沒有空間的人的乏力。

130
00:27:07,000 --> 00:27:12,000
Reading it this way carries a sense of understanding and support.

131
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:16,000
這個分擔不是為了自己的喜悅而去證明自己。

132
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:28,000
Moreover, bearing others' failings isn't your own joy or to prove yourself. Look how great I am, how smart, how clever I am.

133
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:39,000
Bearing others' failings isn't about proving how capable we are, how capable I am, but to bring joy to the person we look after.

134
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:49,000
去分擔不是去證明自己有多能幹,而是去令對方得喜悅。為什麼他們會喜悅呢?

135
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:54,000
因為他們在無力的時候是有人得到陪伴和體諒。

136
00:27:54,000 --> 00:28:02,000
Why would they feel joy? Because in their powerlessness, someone is there for them, someone understands them.

137
00:28:02,000 --> 00:28:08,000
Bearing others' failings is meant to bring them benefit, that is, good.

138
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:15,000
To build them up so that they may later become someone who is able to take care of others.

139
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:24,000
分擔是為了叫人得益處,叫他們被就做,成為有能力去分擔其他人的軟弱。

140
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:31,000
See, this statement clearly explains what it means to be a good person who loves one another.

141
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:39,000
And also what a good church is. A church where people love one another is truly a good church.

142
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:45,000
這句話就清楚去講出了在乎他人的人是在乎他人的好人。

143
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:51,000
這裏講到好的教會裏面,人是在乎其他的人,這個就是一個好的教會。

144
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:53,000
I want to share a secret.

145
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,000
我想同大家分享一個秘密。

146
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:58,000
The book of Romans called Isaiah actually thirteen times.

147
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:03,000
在羅馬書中引用了以塞亞書很多次。

148
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,000
Isaiah is like a backbone of the book of Romans.

149
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:09,000
以塞亞書就是羅馬書的一個骨幹。

150
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:11,000
In Isaiah, last chapter,

151
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:16,000
以塞亞書最後一章Gory appears thirteen times.

152
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:19,000
榮耀講到了有十三次。

153
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:25,000
It talks about the people of all nations and languages, they will come and see God's glory

154
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:33,000
and to the distant islands that have not heard God's fame and seen God's glory.

155
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:37,000
They will proclaim my glory among the nations.

156
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:46,000
耶和華得榮耀豐盛的榮耀,列國的榮耀我的榮耀,漢建我的榮耀,我的榮耀存仰在列國。

157
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:50,000
In the last verse in Romans, it says,

158
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:53,000
在羅馬書最後幾節又這樣講,

159
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:57,000
May God give you the same attitude of might.

160
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:02,000
With one might and one voice, you may glorify God.

161
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:08,000
Accept one another in order to bring glory to God,

162
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:13,000
so that the Gentiles, the unbelievers, may glorify God.

163
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:18,000
願你們彼此同心,效法基督,一心一口榮耀神,

164
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:24,000
要彼此接納,使榮耀歸於神,叫外邦人因他憐憫而榮耀神。

165
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:29,000
Glory, glory and glory, one might and one voice brings glory to God.

166
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:32,000
Accepting one another brings glory to God.

167
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:39,000
When we are united and accepting one another, unbelievers will glorify God.

168
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:44,000
榮耀榮耀榮耀,彼此同心,一心一口就能夠榮耀神,

169
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:50,000
彼此去接納就能夠使榮耀同神,彼此用心,一心一口,

170
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:54,000
彼此接納就能叫人,叫未信的人去榮耀神。

171
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:59,000
This kind of church is truly a good church, a church that glorifies God.

172
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:03,000
那麼這個教會就是一個好的教會,就是一個榮耀神的教會。

173
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:08,000
See, every famous restaurant has a signature dish, right?

174
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:12,000
每一間出名的餐廳相信它都是一些招牌菜。

175
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:15,000
They are most well-known and special food.

176
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:21,000
If you go to, let's say, Michelin two-star or three-star restaurant,

177
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:26,000
the chef will proudly to say, "Hey, this is our best signature dish."

178
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:29,000
當你可能去到米芝蓮兩粒星、三粒星的餐廳,

179
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:33,000
那些廚師都很驕傲地告訴你,這個就是我們的招牌菜了。

180
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:37,000
So if I ask you, what is the signature dish of our church?

181
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:40,000
如果我問你,你覺得我們教的招牌菜是什麼呢?

182
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:45,000
Could it be the cute but noisy kid playing upstairs on level two?

183
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:49,000
你會不會覺得我們二樓樓上很吵的一班小朋友呢?

184
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:52,000
Or maybe when church lunches start again,

185
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:55,000
our laughing and delicious meal will be our signature dish.

186
00:31:55,000 --> 00:32:00,000
會不會是遲些我們將會又有的愛心午飯就是我們的招牌菜呢?

187
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:06,000
Or do some of us even think that the three pastors are the signature dishes?

188
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:10,000
或者大家會不會覺得我們三位牧者就是我們的招牌菜呢?

189
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:14,000
But well, we are not that exactly young and trendy anymore.

190
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:16,000
我們也不再年輕了。

191
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:19,000
原本的翻譯是我們都已經不是小鮮肉了。

192
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:24,000
I truly believe that, my friend, every one of us,

193
00:32:24,000 --> 00:32:29,000
every part of the church, we are the signature dish.

194
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:35,000
我相信大家教會的每一個肢體都是我們的招牌菜。

195
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:39,000
Each of us let others, the unbelievers,

196
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:43,000
taste the love of God and the mercy of Christ Jesus.

197
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:48,000
每一個我們的肢體裏面都被其他人去體驗到

198
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:50,000
主耶穌基督的愛和憐憫。

199
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:54,000
We all took this picture together last December.

200
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:58,000
我們去年一起拍了這張照片。

201
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:03,000
Today's Bible passage, you see, includes many names.

202
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:06,000
今天我們的經文有很多的人名出現。

203
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:10,000
They are all the people who faithfully serve God.

204
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:13,000
這些人也是一些很忠心服侍主的人。

205
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:17,000
But similarly, in our church, I would say, we also have many names.

206
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:19,000
在教會裏面,我們也有很多的人名。

207
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:26,000
We have many chains, many wongs, many phones, many trousers.

208
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:32,000
我們有姓陳,姓馮,姓何,姓趙,什麼人都有。

209
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,000
我們有很多不同姓氏的人。

210
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:40,000
People who open their homes together at church, together at home.

211
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:45,000
有很多頂姊妹開放他們的家庭在家裏面。

212
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:47,000
There are some people who work hard for the Lord.

213
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:50,000
他在主裏面很熱心去侍奉。

214
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:55,000
We also have people who have given up much for Jesus Christ.

215
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:59,000
同樣也有很多人為主放下很多的事情。

216
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:01,000
The point I really want to make is,

217
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:04,000
you guys are the signature dish.

218
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:09,000
今天我想說,每一個肢體都是我們教會的招牌菜。

219
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:13,000
May this message help us, each of us, become a good person.

220
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:16,000
And together, we become a good church.

221
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:19,000
That brings glory to our good Father.

222
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:23,000
願以今天的信息去幫助我們每一個人都成為一個好人,

223
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:27,000
一起去成就一個好的教會,去榮耀我們的神。

224
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:28,000
Let us pray.

225
00:34:28,000 --> 00:34:30,000
我們低頭禱告。

226
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:32,000
Dear Lord, thank you for your work today.

227
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:34,000
Help us to trust you more each day.

228
00:34:34,000 --> 00:34:37,000
And to live out our faith and love.

229
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:41,000
親愛的主,感謝你今天藉著你的話語對我們說話。

230
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:44,000
求你幫助我們每天去信靠你,

231
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:46,000
以愛心去活出我們的信仰。

232
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:48,000
Fill our heart with your love,

233
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:52,000
so we can care for one another with grace and kindness.

234
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:56,000
As we go, let our lives reflect your light.

235
00:34:56,000 --> 00:35:00,000
求你把你的愛充滿我們的心,

236
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:03,000
使我們能夠以恩慈和憐憫彼此相待。

237
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:05,000
And in Jesus' name we pray. Amen.

238
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:07,000
求父主耶穌基督聖名之求。

239
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,000
阿們。

